<title>UK: BT prices $500 mln five-year bond increase.</title>
<headline>BT prices $500 mln five-year bond increase.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following increase for British Telecommunications Plc, announced earlier by joint lead managers Merrill Lynch International and SBC Warburg, has been priced.</p>
<p>The original $1.0 billion deal was launched on April 8 at 15 b.p. spread.</p>
<p>+ + +</p>
<p> AMT	  $500 MLN  COUPON     6.75	MATURITY    25.APR.02</p>
<p> TYPE	 STRAIGHT  ISS PRICE  100.545   PAY DATE    25.APR.97</p>
<p> FULL FEES  1.875     REOFFER    98.92     SPREAD	+12 BP</p>
<p> MOODY	AA1	 LISTING    LONDON    PAY FREQ    ANNUAL</p>
<p> S&amp;P	  AAA	 DENOMS (K) 1-10-100  SALE LIMITS US/GB</p>
<p> NEG PLG    NO	  CRS DEFLT  YES	 FORCE MAJ   IPMA 2</p>
<p> GOV LAW    ENGLISH   HOME CTRY  BRITAIN   TAX PROVS   STANDARD</p>
<p> MGT/UND    0.25	SELL CONC  1.625     PRAECIPUUM  NONE</p>
